text: Luhanka () is a municipality in Central Finland, Finland. About 765 people lived there in February 2014. The municipalities located next to Luhanka are Hartola, Joutsa, Jyväskylä, Jämsä, Kuhmoinen and Sysmä. Originally Luhanka was part of Sysmä. Later it was made into its own municipality in 1864. Luhanka is a popular place for summer cottages. ==Famouse people== * Composer Toni Edelmann lives in Luhanka. * Writer Kreetta Onkeli spent her childhood at Luhanka. ==Other websites== * Community website Category:Municipalities of Central Finland
